                "summary": "Create requirements document for films feature",
                "file_text": "# Requirements Document\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis feature enables the site owner to track and manage films watched using their Cineworld Unlimited pass. The system will allow for detailed film information including metadata (director, cast, release year, poster image), personal ratings, viewing dates, and cinema locations. This helps the site owner maintain a record of their cinema experiences and share film recommendations with visitors.\n\n## Glossary\n\n- **Film Tracking System**: The complete feature set for managing watched films on the website\n- **Film Entry**: A document representing a single film with its metadata and viewing information\n- **Cineworld Unlimited**: A cinema subscription pass that allows unlimited film viewing\n- **Cinema Location**: The specific Cineworld venue where the film was watched\n- **Viewing Date**: The date when the film was watched at the cinema\n- **Personal Rating**: A numerical score (1-5) representing the site owner's personal rating of the film\n- **Film Poster**: The official promotional image for the film\n- **IMDB Link**: A link to the film's Internet Movie Database page\n- **Genre Tags**: Categorisation labels for film genres (Action, Drama, Comedy, etc.)\n- **Director**: The person who directed the film\n- **Cast**: Key actors featured in the film\n- **Release Year**: The year the film was originally released\n- **Runtime**: The duration of the film in minutes\n- **Certificate**: The age rating/classification of the film (U, PG, 12A, 15, 18)\n- **Personal Notes**: Private viewing notes visible only when authenticated in Sanity Studio\n- **Recommendation Status**: Whether the site owner would recommend the film to others\n- **Meta Description**: Custom description text for search engine results pages\n- **Meta Title**: Custom page title for search engine results and browser tabs\n- **OG Image**: Open Graph image for social media sharing previews\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement 1\n\n**User Story:** As a site owner, I want to create film entries with comprehensive metadata, so that I can properly document the films I've watched\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the film title\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the director name\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for key cast members\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the release year\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the film's runtime in minutes\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the film certificate (U, PG, 12A, 15, 18)\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide an optional field for the IMDB URL\n8. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide an image upload field for the film poster\n9. THE Film Tracking System SHALL generate a URL-friendly slug from the film title\n10. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a genre tags field for categorising films\n\n### Requirement 2\n\n**User Story:** As a site owner, I want to record my cinema viewing experience, so that I can track when and where I watched each film\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the viewing date\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for the Cineworld cinema location\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for my personal rating (1-5)\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide an optional field for personal viewing notes\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field to indicate if I would recommend the film\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL validate that the viewing date is not in the future\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL require a rating for each film entry\n\n### Requirement 3\n\n**User Story:** As a site owner, I want to write reviews and thoughts about films, so that I can share my opinions with visitors\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a rich text field for film review content\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL support standard formatting (headings, bold, italic, lists)\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL support embedded images within reviews\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL support external links within reviews\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a field for key takeaways or memorable moments\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow marking content as AI-generated if applicable\n\n### Requirement 4\n\n**User Story:** As a site visitor, I want to browse films by different criteria, so that I can discover recommendations based on my interests\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display films in a paginated list view\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow sorting by rating (highest first)\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow sorting by viewing date (most recent first)\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow sorting by release year (newest first)\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow filtering by genre tags\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow filtering by cinema location\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL allow filtering by recommendation status\n8. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display film poster, title, rating, and viewing date in list view\n\n### Requirement 5\n\n**User Story:** As a site visitor, I want to view detailed information about a specific film, so that I can read the full review and viewing details\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide individual film detail pages\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display all film metadata (title, director, cast, year, runtime, certificate)\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display the film poster image\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display the personal rating with star visualisation\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display the viewing date and cinema location\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display the full review content\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display key takeaways if provided\n8. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display recommendation status\n9. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a link to IMDB if available\n10. THE Film Tracking System SHALL show related films based on genre or director\n\n### Requirement 6\n\n**User Story:** As a site owner, I want the films feature to integrate seamlessly with my existing site, so that it maintains consistency with other content types\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL follow the same URL structure as books (/films, /films/[slug])\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL use the same navigation patterns as existing content\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL support draft mode for preview functionality\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL support Sanity Presentation Studio for visual editing\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL generate appropriate meta tags for SEO\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL generate Open Graph tags for social sharing\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL be responsive across all device sizes\n8. THE Film Tracking System SHALL follow the site's existing design system and components\n\n### Requirement 7\n\n**User Story:** As a site owner, I want to track cinema statistics, so that I can see patterns in my viewing habits\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. THE Film Tracking System SHALL provide a statistics overview page\n2. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display total films watched\n3. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display films watched by month/year\n4. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display most visited cinema locations\n5. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display average rating given\n6. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display genre distribution\n7. THE Film Tracking System SHALL display viewing frequency trends\n8. THE Film Tracking System SHALL be accessible from the main films navigation\n\n## Technical Requirements\n\nAll implementation must follow the standards defined in `.kiro/specs/technical-standards.md`, including:\n\n- ESLint compliance with project configuration\n- British English spelling and terminology\n- TypeScript strict mode compliance\n- Next.js App Router patterns\n- Sanity CMS integration patterns\n- Responsive design principles\n- Accessibility standards\n- Security best practices\n\n## Success Criteria\n\nThe feature will be considered successful when:\n\n1. Film entries can be created and managed through Sanity Studio\n2. Public film listing and detail pages are functional and responsive\n3. Sorting and filtering capabilities work as specified\n4. Statistics page provides meaningful insights\n5. All pages have appropriate SEO meta tags\n6. Feature integrates seamlessly with existing site navigation\n7. Code passes all ESLint checks and follows project standards\n8. Feature works in both draft and published modes"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
